after the&s;e Things; I pray God increa&s;e
the Knowledge of him&s;elf in your Mind, and
comfort you with the Hope of his Pre&s;ence and
Ble&s;&s;ing.</P>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>La. Amen.</SPEAKER>
<P>I thank you, <HI>William.</HI></P>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Will.</SPEAKER>
<P>Look you now, Sir, <HI>and't plea&s;e you,</HI> did
