</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Bro.</SPEAKER>
<P>Why, you won't pretend this is without
Cau&s;e?</P>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Sist.</SPEAKER>
<P>Truly, Brother, I do not &s;ee any Cau&s;e
you have to be offended with your Child; it's true,
you brought a very fine young Gentleman to court
her, and I know you were plea&s;ed with the Thoughts
<PB N="107" REF="114">
of &s;uch an Alliance in your Family; his E&s;tate, his
Per&s;on, his Character, were all plea&s;ing; but
here's che Ca&s;e, your Daughter has been religiou&s;ly
